==English==
===Adverb===
'''awhile'''

#For some time; for a short time.
#:''Sit with me awhile.''

====Usage note====
*Since '''awhile''' means "for a while", it is never used with a preceding preposition.  When preceded by a preposition, the correct form is "a while", as two words.

